EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to wildlife; requiring the Board of Wildlife
Commissioners to adopt regulations providing for the
issuance of salvage permits; providing an exception to
certain prohibitions relating to wildlife; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the Board of Wildlife Commissioners to establish certain
2 policies and adopt certain regulations to carry out and to enforce certain provisions
3 relating to wildlife. (NRS 501.181) Section 1 of this bill: (1) requires the Commission
4 to adopt regulations requiring the Department of Wildlife to issue salvage permits that
5 authorize a person to salvage and collect any wildlife killed as a result of a vehicle
6 collision or any other incidental event; and (2) prohibits the Commission from
7 prescribing a fee for the issuance of a salvage permit. Section 1 additionally provides
8 that the Commission may, by regulation, prohibit the Department from issuing
9 salvage permits if any wildlife in this State is confirmed to have tested positive for
10 chronic wasting disease.
11 In addition to regular hunting licenses and trapping licenses, existing law requires
12 a person to have a tag to hunt certain species of game mammals and authorizes the
13 Commission to require tags in certain other circumstances. (NRS 502.130) If tags are
14 required, existing law prohibits a person from possessing any of that species, or parts
15 thereof, without the correct tag. (NRS 502.150) Subject to certain exceptions, existing
16 law prohibits any person from having in his or her control any wildlife or any part
17 thereof, during the time when the killing of such wildlife is prohibited. (NRS 503.030)
18 Sections 2 and 3 of this bill provide that a person holding a salvage permit issued by
19 regulation of the Commission adopted pursuant to section 1 is exempted from those
20 prohibitions.
