1 Section 1. Chapter 501 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Commission shall adopt regulations requiring the
4 Department to issue salvage permits that authorize a person to
5 salvage and collect any wildlife killed as a result of a vehicle
6 collision or any other incidental event. The regulations adopted by
7 the Commission pursuant to this section may prohibit the
8 Department from issuing salvage permits if any wildlife in this
9 State is confirmed to have tested positive for chronic wasting
10 disease.
11 2. The Commission may not prescribe a fee for the issuance
12 of a salvage permit pursuant to the regulations of the Commission
13 adopted pursuant to this section.
14 Sec. 2. NRS 502.150 is hereby amended to read as follows:
15 502.150 1. [Whenever] Except as otherwise provided in the
16 regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant to section 1 of
17 this act, whenever tags are required for any species of wildlife, it is
18 unlawful to have any of that species in possession without the
19 correct tag. Before transporting any species of wildlife, or parts
20 thereof, for which a tag is required, the holder of:
21 (a) A paper tag must attach the tag to the animal; or
22 (b) An electronic tag must validate the tag in accordance with
23 the regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant to
24 NRS 502.160.
25  Possession of any species of wildlife, or parts thereof, for which a
26 tag is required without an attached or validated tag, as applicable, is
27 prima facie evidence that the game is illegally taken and possessed.
28 2. It is unlawful to remove any tag from any wildlife for reuse
29 or to be in possession of excess tags or used tags.
30 3. [Whenever] Except as otherwise provided in the
31 regulations adopted by the Commission pursuant to section 1 of
32 this act, whenever tags are required for any species of fur-bearing
33 mammal, possession of a pelt of that species without the tag
34 attached thereto or validated, as applicable, is prima facie evidence
35 that such pelt is illegally taken and possessed.
